reviews.review_text:
Short but Sweet The three Jerry tunes just kick ass!  Deep Elem, Dire Wolf and CR&S are top notch, Jerry is letting it rip - nice and loud in the mix.   There are a couple points in CR&S that got me to jump up and shout - scared my wife a little.

The rest is so-so.  

The Joan stuff is cringe worthy.

The sound is really good when it isn't really bad.  The mix seems to go in and out a bit.  Luckily the three Jerry tunes all sound great.  And Jerry is way loud in the mix - always a good thing for me.

I was at this gig and do remember it having a nice edge to it.  And if I remember correctly (only a 70% chance) this wasn't the usual big GD stage set-up...gives it a small venue rock band sound.  It was a funky little exhibition hall with only a few folks in attendance.
